==English==
===Noun===
'''langet'''
# a long thin strip of metal (usually either two or four) extending from the head of a staff weapon (such as a [[Wikipedia:halberd|halberd]]) down a certain length of the wooden shaft, secured with nails or screws and designed to prevent splitting or breakage of the wood.
# in some [[Wikipedia:sword|swords]], an extension of the [[Wikipedia:hilt|guard]] located on both flats of the [[Wikipedia:blade|blade]], designed to fit tightly over the mouth of a [[Wikipedia:scabbard|scabbard]] and prevent accidental unsheathing.